<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12213o"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12213o">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12213o"> 213(o)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Easter Eve &mdash; if <font face="wake">+</font> / doesn&apos;t rise!</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">J.-C. Lawson, o. l., p. 573: Happening to be in some village of Euboea during Holy Week, he had been struck by the emotion which the Good Friday service evoked; and observing the next day the same general air of gloom and despondency, he questioned an old woman about it; whereupon she replied: &ldquo;Of course I am anxious; for <mark>if Christ does not rise to morrow, we shall have no corn this year</mark>.&rdquo; <small> Stefan Czarnowski, <a name="SCSP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SCSP"><cite title="source">Le culte des h&eacute;ros et ses conditions sociale: saint Patrick, h&eacute;ros nationale de l'Irlande</cite></a> (1919) LXIV, note 1</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
